Her recent work on LLM biases received a best paper award at ACL 2025. In April 2026, she gave a talk on "Stateless Yet Not Forgetful: Implicit Memory as a Hidden Channel in LLMs" at the Trustworthy AI Seminar Series, presenting work on how LLMs can carry state across independent interactions.

