# Progress from our Frontier Red Team

**Title:** Progress from our Frontier Red Team

**Date:** March 19, 2025

**Authors:** Not explicitly named (published by Anthropic's Frontier Red Team)

## Summary

Anthropic's red team evaluated national security risks from frontier AI models across four releases, finding that Claude displays early warning signs of rapid progress in cybersecurity and biology capabilities. The models now perform at undergraduate levels in some cybersecurity domains and expert-level knowledge in certain biological areas, though they remain below thresholds requiring substantially elevated national security concerns. The assessment emphasizes that real-world risks depend on multiple factors beyond AI capabilities, including physical constraints and specialized equipment.

## Methods and Findings

**Cybersecurity Evaluations:**
- Claude improved from "high school to undergraduate level" in Capture The Flag exercises within one year
